dd
	if - input file
	of - output file
	bs - block size written at a time

	dd bs=4M if=path-to-file.iso of=/dev/sdb (not /dev/sdb1!)

	Delete all data on a device:
	dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sdb

	Specify amount of megabites to be copied, starting from the beginning of the file:
	dd if=/dev/zero of=test-file bs=1M count=100

dcfldd - enchanced dd

file - reads the first 8 bites from a file and returns the MIME type recorded in them

	file --mime-type script.rb

