ssh - Secure Shell

The following environment variables are created after SSH login
and hold information about the SSH client's address, incoming,
outgoing port and TTY:
SSH_CLIENT
SSH_CONNECTION
SSH_TTY

	ssh -A user@hostname -i public_key - forward public key to use in subsequent SSH connections from the remote location

scp - secure copy - copy files to a remote server

	scp -P 22 archive.tar.gz user@server.com:/home/$USER
	scp -P 22 -i id_rsa archive.tar.gz user@server.com:/home/$USER
	scp -i id_rsa -r log-files/ user@server.com -p 22 # to copy a directory

	from remote to local:
	scp user@server.com:/path/to/file /home/$USER/
	scp -p - preserve mtime, ctime, atime and other properties

