rsync

	options source destination

	rsync -z - compress files during transfer
	rsync -n - dry run
	rsync -v - verbose
	rsync -P - adds a progress bar and gives the opportunity to resume
			   stopped transfers
	rsync --progress - adds a progress bar
	rsync --chmod +x - add executable mode to new files

	exclude a subdirectory with a particular name:
	rsync --exclude misc/ backup_1/ backup_2/
	This will exclude any directory named misc/ anywhere in the copied tree of files,
	not only in the underlying directory!

	use the ssh protocol:
	rsync -e ssh remote_host_name:remote_file local_file

	set bandwidth limit:
	rsync --bwlimit=2000 <source> <dest> (this will set the bandwidth to 2MB)

	set log file:
	rsync --log-file=rsync-log.txt

	send a file over SSH:
	rsync -avzhe --progress 'ssh -i .ssh/cvetomir_rsa_key' internal-v2.tar.gz root@193.203.198.77:/home/

