	Issue with vSphere on Windows Server 2012 x64 - server loses networking gateway:
	Fix:
		choose only one NIC with E1000E adapter (equivalent to Intel Pro 1000 NIC)

	Insert licence through the console:
	https://vmexpo.wordpress.com/2014/02/04/how-to-renew-your-expire-esxi-license/

vSphere

	VMDK Disk types:
	Thin Provision - Similar to 'Dynamically allocated' in VirtualBox.
	Thick/Lazy-zeroed provision - all space allocated upon creaton. Data is not
								  zero-written on device. Stale data may be present
								  on the HDD.

	Eager Zeroed Thick - all space allocated (similar to Fixed size in VirtualBox)
						The entire disk space is unavailable for other virtual machines
						The difference with Thick/Lazy-zeroed is that all space is
						zero-written before allocating space for the new VMKD disk.

	How to create a VMVisor bootable ISO:
	https://pubs.vmware.com/vsphere-60/index.jsp?topic=%2Fcom.vmware.vsphere.install.doc%2FGUID-33C3E7D5-20D0-4F84-B2E3-5CD33D32EAA8.html


