Differences:
	*mod_php (DSO) - Runs PHP as part of Apache. PHP is run directly in the same process as the
		       	 Apache server. all work on files will be done as the Apache user which therefore
			 must have permissions on the files. Often the files on your site are owned by users
			 other than that running the webserver. Therefore this configuration is unsuitable for
			 a shared environment.

		- thread-safety
		- non-thread-safety

	*CGI 		- PHP is run as a separate cgi process, in a executable outside Apache's
			  	Requires more CPU time than mod_php.

	*suPHP		- Runs PHP outside of the Apache process as the user who owns the files.

	*FastCGI	- Same as suPHP except each PHP process has its own memory pool

	*suEXEC

	*Spawn FCGI

