SMTP

SMTP cannot run over UDP, because UDP is a stateless protocol.
SMTP is connection-oriented.

SMTP Header Fields

Reputation Rank

We can use TLS over SMTP on port 25, not just 465. This is good for the reputation rank of the
Email service providers. Some big SMTP hosts won't receive mail from SMTP on port 25 if the sender
doesn't use TLS.

SPF record:

~all - makes the rules not obligatory
-all - makes the rules in the SPF record obligatory

https://senderscore.org/
https://returnpath.com

Cisco's Mail sending reputation data website:
http://senderbase.com/

http://spamcop.net/
http://mxtoolbox.net/

http://multirbl.valli.org/lookup/193.203.198.10.html

We can configure the SMTP daemon to change the MSA port dynamically. Some MUAs can query the DNS
for the MSA port dyniamically (like Evolution).

The mailbox authentication for a mailbox happens when communicating with the MSA.

postconf - dump postfix config

