POST - Power On Safe Test - The BIOS initializes the hardware (including keyboard, mouse and screen)
	and tests the main memory. This happens after the power is turned on. Once the POST is completed,
	the system control passes from the BIOS to the boot loader.

MBR - Master Boot Record - the first sector of a disk that designates it is a bootable device

